description:
Create test fixtures in cmd/gemini-slave/testdata/:

1. `small_input.go` - ~1KB Go file for basic tests
2. `large_input.go` - Generated 50KB Go file (the original failing case)
3. `error_traceback.txt` - Sample Python traceback for debugger protocol
4. `go_module.txt` - Multi-file Go module content for deps/api-surface

The large_input.go should be generated programmatically to ensure consistent size:

```go
// In test setup
func generateLargeInput(size int) string {
    var b strings.Builder
    b.WriteString("package main\n\n")
    for i := 0; b.Len() < size; i++ {
        fmt.Fprintf(&b, "func Function%d() {\n\t// Implementation %d\n}\n\n", i, i)
    }
    return b.String()
}
```

Key: The 50KB test MUST work reliably - this is the original bug.
